<div type="definition">
<p>SITUATION characterised by LACK of WARFARE.</p>
<p>[[FRIEDEN]]</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for universal peace is tài píng 太平, and this word became current from Han times onwards.</p>
<p>2. Hé 和 is occasionally used to refer to peaceful conditions.</p>
<p>3. Chéng 成 is a technical term meaning "to sue for peace" and is thus marginal to this group.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>和平</p>
<p>清平</p>
<p>相安無事</p>
<p>西線無戰事</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
